name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(bslib)
library(ggplot2)
library(gt)

ui <- page_sidebar(
  title = "Glucose Transport Rates",
  sidebar = sidebar(
    sliderInput("glucose", "Glucose Concentration (mmol/L) (Note: 1 mmol/L = 18 mg/dL)",
                min = 0, max = 40, value = 5, step = 0.1),
    checkboxInput("insulin", "Insulin Present", value = FALSE)
  ),
  card(
    card_header("Transport Rates (mmol/min)"),
    card_body(
      plotOutput("rate_plot", height = "1000px")
    )
  ),
  card(
    card_header("GLUT Transporters Information"),
    card_body(
      gt_output("info_table")
    )
  )
)

server <- function(input, output) {
  
  # Table data
  output$info_table <- render_gt({
    data.frame(
      Transporter = c("GLUT-1", "GLUT-2", "GLUT-3", "GLUT-4"),
      `Tissue distribution` = c(
        "RBCs, blood-brain barrier",
        "Small intestine, Pancreatic beta cells, Liver and kidney",
        "Neurons",
        "Adipose tissue, skeletal muscle and heart"
      ),
      Km  = c("~7mmol/L","~23mmol/L","~1.4mmol/L","~5mmol/L"),
      Function = c(
        "Glucose uptake at basal conditions",
        "Absorption of glucose, Allows free entry of glucose into the beta cells and liver",
        "High-affinity uptake of glucose by brain and nervous tissue even at lower concentrations",
        "Insulin stimulated uptake of glucose"
      )
    ) |>
      gt() |>
      tab_header(title = "GLUT Transporters Information") |>
      fmt_markdown(columns = everything()) |>
      tab_options(
        table.font.size = "large",
        column_labels.font.weight = "bold"
      )
  })
  # Michaelis-Menten equation: V = (Vmax * [S]) / (Km + [S])
  calculate_rate <- function(glucose, km, vmax) {
    (vmax * glucose) / (km + glucose)
  }
  
  output$rate_plot <- renderPlot({
    # Calculate GLUT4 rate based on insulin presence
    glut4_rate <- if(input$insulin) {
      calculate_rate(input$glucose, km = 5, vmax = 0.02)
    } else {
      0
    }
    
    rates <- c(
      calculate_rate(input$glucose, km = 7, vmax = 0.035),   # GLUT1
      calculate_rate(input$glucose, km = 23, vmax = 0.092), # GLUT2
      calculate_rate(input$glucose, km = 1.4, vmax = 0.040),# GLUT3
      glut4_rate   # GLUT4
    )
    
    data <- data.frame(
      Transporter = factor(c("GLUT1", "GLUT2", "GLUT3", "GLUT4")),
      Rate = rates

    )
    
    ggplot(data, aes(x = Transporter, y = Rate, fill = Transporter)) +
      geom_bar(stat = "identity") +

      labs(
        title = paste("Glucose Transport Rates at", input$glucose, "mmol/L"),
        y = "Transport Rate (mmol/min)",
        x = "Glucose Transporter"
      ) +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(
        legend.position = "none",
        axis.title = element_text(size = 16),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 14),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold"),
        text = element_text(size = 14))
      
  })
}

shinyApp(ui, server)
